Since this is for debugging, how about having a c_str() equivalent that
actually does a strdup() like ?

Basically:

char *gpr_string_from_slice(const gpr_slice *slice) {
  char *ret = gpr_malloc(GPR_SLICE_SIZE(slice) + 1);
  memcpy(ret, GPR_SLICE_PTR(slice), GPR_SLICE_SIZE(slice));
  ret[GPR_SLICE_SIZE(slice)] = 0;
  return ret;
}

